1 Details about all EVAR performed

1.1 Timescale covered and number of EVAR

  • This document covers EVAR performed between 1996-09-19 and 2019-12-10 for any indication
  • This comprises 1035 EVAR
  • Of these, the numbers are split among the Health Boards as detailed below:

All years; FV = Forth Valley, GG & C = Greater Glasgow and Clyde

1.2 Indication

1.2.1 Number of EVAR for each indication

  • Both ruptured and symptomatic aneurysms are judged by available clinical information
  • "Open repair issue" is usually pseudoaneurysm formation

1.2.2 Numbers of EVAR for each indication at each site

1.3 Gender

1.3.1 Number of EVAR performed by gender

  • 10% of EVAR have been performed in women

1.3.2 Number of EVAR performed by gender at each site

  • In GG & C, 10.4% of EVAR have been performed in women
  • In FV, 5.7% of EVAR have been performed in women
  • In Lothian, 9.7% of EVAR have been performed in women

1.4 Age

  • Boxplots are used in this section
  • Here is a reminder of what a boxplot displays:
    • The â€˜boxâ€™ represents the interquartile range (IQR) of the data
    • In other words, 50% of the patients fall between this age range
    • The thick black horizontal line is the median age
    • The thin black vertical lines extend to the upper and lower limits of age
    • Black dots represent outliers (above or below 3 x IQR)
